About Socket Head Screws

More

Alloy Steel Socket Head Screws

Fully Threaded
Partially Threaded

These screws are made from an alloy steel that's stronger than Grade 8 steel. Length is measured from under the head.

Black-oxide steel screws are mildly corrosion resistant in dry environments.

Zinc-plated steel screws are more corrosion resistant than black-oxide screws for use in wet environments.

Zinc-aluminum-coated steel screws are 40 times as corrosion resistant as zinc-plated screws and are also known as Magni-coated screws. They withstand 1,000 hours of salt spray per ASTM B117.

For technical drawings and 3-D models, click on a part number.
